00:22:17.036 --> 00:22:20.686
you can see a lot of blue here. And so that means that the peaks have kind of

405
00:22:20.696 --> 00:22:24.356
spread apart, and it's a good signal, and that would indicate strong

406
00:22:24.396 --> 00:22:28.256
binding. And here's what a few just peaks would look

407
00:22:28.276 --> 00:22:29.586
like. So here's a transition from this

408
00:22:30.476 --> 00:22:33.676
pure red over here to blue. Here's red to blue, and this is a peak that's really

409
00:22:33.716 --> 00:22:33.956
not

410
00:22:34.876 --> 00:22:35.826
affected that much.

411
00:22:37.206 --> 00:22:40.736
And so we looked at 1,920 compounds originally,

412
00:22:41.416 --> 00:22:44.696
through these deconvolution steps. We got down to 37 hits.

413
00:22:44.716 --> 00:22:48.176
We've been working on this now for about three years.

414
00:22:48.296 --> 00:22:49.796
And I'm just going to show you,

